1) Hero image uploader (High impact — small/medium)
Why: Makes Showcase and Editable themes feel modern and lets users personalize their profile immediately.
Files to touch: ProfileEditor.tsx, ThemeShowcase.tsx, ThemeEditable.tsx, route.ts.
Steps:
Add a file input + preview in ProfileEditor.
Call /api/uploads/signed to get a signed PUT URL (existing route).
PUT the image to the signed URL and set config.heroBackground to the uploaded URL.
Call updateProfileConfig(config) to persist.
Edge cases: large files (client-side size limit), image type validation, show upload progress, fallback if signed route not configured.
ETA: 2–6 hours.

2) Migrate uploads to S3/CDN (Medium impact — medium effort)
Why: Scales storage and speeds delivery (CDN), necessary for public profiles and large files.
Files to touch: server/s3.ts (or create), route.ts, model fields referencing file URLs.
Steps:
Add server-side S3 helpers (signed URL generation).
Update upload route to generate S3 signed URLs.
Replace uses of /public/uploads/* with external CDN URLs in profile rendering.
Env: S3_BUCKET, S3_REGION, S3_KEY, S3_SECRET, CDN_URL.
ETA: 1–2 days (incl. testing).


